After the COVID-19 pandemic started, Javiera Morales Daviu, a psychologist and art therapist in Barcelona, lost most sources of income as it was hard to arrange face-to-face therapy during a lockdown. To alleviate the stress caused by the pandemic, she and her partner moved to a rural area and started doing therapy online. In this video, Javiera talks about how she's changed her working mode under the pandemic and regained the rhythmÂ of her life.